Citation.sAbstract: The (p, rho, T) properties and apparent molar volumes of CaCl2 in methanol at T = (298.15 to 398.15) K, at pressures up to 40 MPa are reported, and apparent molar volumes have been evaluated. The experimental (p, rho, T) values were described by an equation of state. The experiments were carried out at m = (0.10819, 0.28529, 0.65879 and 2.39344) mol * kg-1 of calcium chloride.
Citation.sTitle: (p, rho , T) properties and apparent molar volumes of CaCl2 in methanol at T=(298.15 to 398.15) K and pressures up to 40 MPa
